The paper focuses on prototyping in software startups, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspects. The study also considers collaboration and customer dimensions, which are relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the importance of a well-defined process, which is relevant to systems and information theory (cs.SI).
